node.title: Two people seriously injured in Auckland disorder incident
node.description: Residents said they heard sirens, a helicopter and what sounded like gunshots.
node.content: ["Two people are seriously injured after a disorder event in Auckland's Clendon Park on Wednesday.\u00a0", "Police were called to the scene around 9:30pm after multiple reports of disorder.\u00a0", "A spokesperson told Newshub police located a number of victims with varying injuries, who were transported to hospital for treatment.\u00a0", "\"Police remain at the scene and continue to investigate the circumstances of the incidents,\" they said.\u00a0", "A St John spokesperson said three ambulances and two rapid response vehicles responded.\u00a0", "\"We assessed and treated two patients in a serious condition who were transported to Middlemore hospital.\"\u00a0", "Residents of the south Auckland suburb said they heard sirens, a helicopter and what sounded like gunshots."]
